author: @priyam66
text: max_length=0 for i in corpus:   length=len(i.split())   if length>max_length:     max_length=length print(max_length)   Please correct me if my below observation is incorrect: The above code will find the maximum length of any sentence in the corpus. for this dataset , it is 47. therefore while padding the sentence, we can choose the maxlen as 47 to avoid truncating the sentence.  In the video, it is chosen as 20 which would truncate the sentences.
